<HL>
   Lubrizol Stock Repurchase
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS LZ
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   CLEVELAND -- Lubrizol Corp. said directors authorized the
specialty chemical concern to repurchase up to two million of
its common shares.
   Lubrizol, which has 36 million shares outstanding, will
make the repurchase on the open market. Lubrizol closed
yesterday at $40.375, up 12.5 cents, in New York Stock
Exchange composite trading.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Separately, Lubrizol announced that Ray A. Andreas was
elected vice president and chief financial officer,
succeeding William T. Beargie, 60, who is retiring. Mr.
Andreas, 45, had been corporate controller and vice
president-finance of the Lubrizol Petroleum Chemicals Co.
unit.
</TEXT>
